      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="lead lead-big"><strong>TUITION FEE FUNDING AND SPONSORSHIP</strong></span></p>
<p>If you have access to funding (from another organisation, employer, etc.), you must email the details to <a href="mailto:registry@qmu.ac.uk%20">registry@qmu.ac.uk.</a> You can also inform us of your sponsor details during the matriculation process.</p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong><img src="?width=580&amp;height=344" alt="A small group of people talking, facing away from the camera, on a sunny day outside" width="580" height="344" data-udi="umb://media/c4a43a9cd0e14ff8ade0015821339f28" /></strong></span></p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>SELF FUNDED STUDENTS</strong></span></p>
<p>If you are personally liable for the payment of any part of your <a href="/{localLink:umb://document/781a0772d20b4e7091629a2db90d5926}" title="Fees and Charges">fees</a>, you can make arrangements to pay by direct debit instalments. <strong>Direct debits</strong> run for <strong>8 month</strong>s from <strong>October</strong> through to <strong>May</strong>, inclusive, and returning students must renew their direct debit details via the Finance Office. Courses starting in the <strong>Second Semester</strong> can pay by direct debit <strong>January</strong> to <strong>August</strong>. You can also set-up a direct debit through the student portal once you have matriculated online.</p>
<p>If paying direct to our bank account, please email <a href="mailto:financeoffice@qmu.ac.uk">financeoffice@qmu.ac.uk</a> for details.</p>
<p>Please ensure your bank deducts all costs of the transfer from your bank account thus ensuring we receive the complete sum required. Please make sure also that you use your <strong>student number</strong> as a reference, followed by your name.</p>
<p><img src="?width=580&amp;height=344" alt="Students playing frisbee on the grass outside Queen Margaret University, Edinburgh" width="580" height="344" data-udi="umb://media/28e061f7de214583ab38c0fcbeddcfc6" /></p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>STUDENT LOANS </strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Please ensure that you have <a href="/current-students/current-students-general-information/matriculation-and-enrolment/">matriculated</a> at least 3 working days before your first payment is due, to ensure payment is made to you in time.</strong></p>
<p>All bursary/student loan payments will be made through the BACS transfer process. Once you have matriculated will we inform the Student Loans Company that you are a registered student for session 2023/24. This will be done automatically.</p>
<p>The Student Loans Company will then arrange for your bursary/student loan payment to be transferred directly into your bank account within <strong>3-5 working days</strong> of receipt of registration notification or the first day of term, whichever is the later.</p>
<p>For Scottish students who have applied to the <a href="https://www.saas.gov.uk/">Student Awards Agency Scotland</a>, student loans and bursaries will be paid on a monthly basis with an additional first payment being made at the start of their course.</p>
<p><strong>If your bank details change</strong>, it is imperative that you immediately inform <strong>both</strong> SAAS and SLC.</p>
<p>If you do not do this your payments could be interrupted.</p>
<p>More details of the monthly payment scheme can be found on the <a href="https://www.saas.gov.uk/" title="Student Awards Agency Scotland">Students Awards Agency Scotland website</a>.</p>
<p><img src="?width=580&amp;height=344" alt="Students relaxing on the grass outside Queen Margaret University Campus, Edinburgh" width="580" height="344" data-udi="umb://media/11da7743e4e4491393986f158c1ea9da" /></p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>STUDENT AWARDS AGENCY SCOTLAND (SAAS)</strong></span></p>
<p>SAAS applications for both Undergraduate and Postgraduate students are now open. Please ensure that you submit your application by <strong>30th June </strong>to ensure your first payment arrives on time. Students must have completed online matriculation 3-5 working days before the first payment is due. More information can be found on the <a href="https://www.saas.gov.uk/" title="Student Awards Agency Scotland">Students Awards Agency Scotland website</a>. Continuing students must submit a new application each year. If you need to contact SAAS, please refer to their <a href="https://www.saas.gov.uk/contact-us">Contact Us</a> page for ways to get in touch.</p>
<p><img src="?width=580&amp;height=344" alt="A student sitting on a sunny bench at Queen Margaret University, Edinburgh" width="580" height="344" data-udi="umb://media/84c69f7bc12f4c56b741e7967797789f" /></p>
<p><strong style="font-size: 16px;">STUDENT FINANCE ENGLAND, WALES AND NORTHERN IRELAND</strong></p>
<p>Student Finance applications are also now open. It’s quick and easy to apply, it should take less than 30 minutes.</p>
<p>Don't worry if you have missed the deadline, you can still apply but funds are not guaranteed for the first week of term. More information, including contact details for each area, can be found on the following web pages:</p>
<p><a href="#everything_you_need_to_know_about_2023_to_2024" data-anchor="#everything_you_need_to_know_about_2023_to_2024">Student Finance England</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.studentfinancewales.co.uk/">Student Finance Wales</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.studentfinanceni.co.uk/">Student Finance Northern Ireland</a></p>]]></Value>
